The paper deals with a new homomorphic encryption scheme based on coding theory, which is a subfield of information theory (cs.IT) and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the hardness of decoding under independent random noise, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR). The paper's technical contributions involve handling encryption error in the homomorphic evaluation process, which could fall under data structures (cs.DS) or machine learning (cs.LG) depending on the specific techniques used.
